Adversarial review (review-1.json):
  Opus 4.7 via Agent tool; verdict: ship; 0 blockers; 4 nits.
  Nits: case-sensitive event slug lookup (current callers use
  uppercase, so latent), JSONB filters use template-cast not
  sql.json (consistent with composio_triggers INSERT and produces
  correct JSONB), state seeded as `{}` not initialState (spec
  deviation; functionally equivalent via adapters' defensive
  re-baseline; avoids api→worker coupling), hand-maintained
  ADAPTER_BACKED_TRIGGERS (one-line PR review catches drift).

Notes / decisions:
  - getTriggerType lookup is cached in-memory (Map) for the process
    lifetime — trigger types are essentially immutable per slug,
    and a fresh Composio lookup per reconcile would add latency to
    automation save. Test seam `setTriggerTypeLookupForTests`
    bypasses both cache and HTTP.
  - resolveTriggerType returns 'webhook' on any error (Composio
    outage, 404 on unknown slug, network failure). Safe degradation
    — operator gets Composio-managed polling instead of a save
    failure.
  - Implementation does NOT call adapter.initialState() at
    registration time as spec literally asks. Instead seeds state=
    {} and lets the adapter's poll() defensive-recovery branch
    re-baseline on first invocation. Functionally equivalent
    (with at most a 1-poll delay before events start firing),
    avoids api/worker package coupling, every adapter F.3-F.8 has
    this branch already.
  - Pre-existing failure in composio.test.ts (assertion drift after
    D.5 added connectionExpired field to the webhook response) was
    fixed in the same commit since it surfaced during this step's
    verify pass and was unrelated to F.9.

Out of scope (lands in F.10):
  - LIVE e2e: chat-authored automation with googlesheets + gmail
    triggers, both route into composio_poll_state, both fire within
    2 min on real events.
